        <h2 class="display-4 text-center ">Variegata</h2>
        <p class="my-4 lead text-center">Variegation is the appearance of differently coloured zones in the leaves and sometimes the stems, of plants. Variegated leaves occur rarely in nature. Species with variegated individuals are sometimes found in the understory of tropical rainforests, and this habitat is the source of a number of variegated house plants.

        The term is also sometimes used to refer to colour zonation in flowers, minerals, and the skin, fur, feathers or scales of animals. </p>
